To concatenate a `List<List<X>>` into a single `List<X>` in C#, you can use the `SelectMany()` method. Here's an example:

```csharp
List<List<X>> listOfLists = new List<List<X>>
{
    new List<X> { new X { Id = 1 }, new X { Id = 2 } },
    new List<X> { new X { Id = 3 }, new X { Id = 4 } }
};

List<X> concatenatedList = listOfLists.SelectMany(list => list).ToList();
```

In this code, we have a `List<List<X>>` called `listOfLists`, which contains multiple nested lists of `X` objects.

To concatenate these lists into a single `List<X>`, we use the `SelectMany()` method. This method flattens the outer list and merges all the inner lists into one sequence. Finally, we call `ToList()` to convert the sequence into a `List<X>`.

